      • applyPullUpMethod

        boolean applyPullUpMethod(java.util.List<java.lang.String> src_classes,
                          java.lang.String method_signature)
        Applies pull up method on the generated type graph.

        References to classes are fully qualified. E.g.:

        class: (PACKAGE_NAME '.')+ CLASS_NAME

        The methods signature is in the following format:

        methodSignature: METHOD_NAME '(' (PARAM_TYPE ',')+ ')'

        Parameters:
        src_classes - List of classes from which a method should be pulled up.
        method_signature - Signature of the method which should be pulled up.
        Returns:
        true iff the application of pull-up method was successful, otherwise false.

      • applyExtractSuperclass

        boolean applyExtractSuperclass(java.util.List<java.lang.String> src_classes,
                               java.util.List<java.lang.String> method_signatures,
                               java.util.List<java.lang.String> field_signatures)
        Applies extract superclass on the given classes and extracts the given methods and fields to a new superclass.

        References to classes are fully qualified. E.g.:

        class: (PACKAGE_NAME '.')+ CLASS_NAME

        The method signatures will be given in the following format:

        methodSignatur: METHOD_NAME '(' (PARAM_TYPE ',')+ ')'

        The field signatures will be given in the following format:

        fieldSignature: FIELD_NAME ':' FIELD_TYPE

        Parameters:
        src_classes - List of classes for which a superclass should be extracted.
        method_signatures - List of the methods which should be extracted
        field_signatures - List of fields which should be extracted
        Returns:
        true iff the application of extract superclass was successful, otherwise false.

      • synchronizeChanges

        boolean synchronizeChanges()
        Synchronizes the java code with the type graph and propagates all changes made in the type graph to the java source code
        Returns:
        true iff all changes have success full be synchronized with the java code, otherwise false.
